This paper deals with the analysis of large-scale social media data to understand human migration patterns. The paper uses tensor decomposition to model human migration as a three-mode tensor, which is a common technique in the field of social informatics (cs.SI). The paper also deals with data processing and analysis, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.SD). The paper's focus on understanding human migration patterns makes it relevant to the field of social sciences (cs.SOC). The paper also uses natural language processing techniques to extract meaningful insights from Twitter data, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper's focus on understanding global migration patterns makes it relevant to the field of cyber-geography (cs.CY).
